<br>
Wizards have a few things to offer meleers, like our stuns and dd's (and a stacking DS, LMAO). In places, like Velious, not only do the mobs have more hps, they also have high MR, so our stuns become less efficient. PLUS, where the hell is our 57 or 58 atun, the impossible one to find?  Also, with the resistances our non-magic based spells are also hitting for less, so what do we do? We get lures, which are BULLSHIT IMHO. Lures do nothing less than make us less efficient as casters. We are supposed to be the efficient nukers, to augment meleers because we can't buff or heal or sow or clarity. They take longer to cast, do less damage and are less efficient in damage. We also have Bane spells, what a crock of crap. We not only have to quest for them, we have to be level 60 to use. What kind of BS is that? That makes all 1% of Wizards more useful in VERY limited situations, plus do you think a group wants to shell out cash for our regents to cast it?<br>
<br>
Without efficiency, we are not extremely useful, therefore folks want us when we are efficient, and that's when combat is about to begin or it's over to take meleers where they need to go next to kill. Thanks for the new TL's, VI. This way I can make cash for my alternate, that assists meleers more efficiently.<br>
<br>
<br>
I wish I had the patience to write more, and all folks could even pay attention that long, cuz this would be one HELL OF A post.<br>
<br>
Soliceia Arcanus ---man, I feel better when I bitch.<br>
